Bank of China May Buy Plane-Leasing Unit From RBS, Times Says

-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 
2011-07-24T07:03:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/bank-of-china-may-buy-plane-leasing-unit-from-rbs-times-says.html
Bank of China Ltd. (3988)  joined the list
of possible buyers for the $5 billion plane-leasing business
from  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS) , the London-based Sunday
Times reported, without saying where it got the information.  General Electric Co. and Terra Firma Capital Partners Ltd.
are among eight companies that have expressed interest for the
Dublin-based aircraft-financing and leasing business, RBS
Aviation Capital, the newspaper said. A spokesman for the
aviation unit confirmed the sale process is under way and
declined to comment further, the Times reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adam Haigh in London at 
